                "Activities": "<section>\n  <h2>Finance Division Activities</h2>\n  <p>The Finance division manages the company's financial operations, procurement, and payment processes. Below are the primary operational activities and how to engage with them.</p>\n\n  <ul class=\"efg-detail\">\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Service\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Procurement and Purchasing</strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">Procurement manages vendor onboarding, sourcing requests, and contract negotiations. For purchases under €25,000, the Requesting Party can submit a Purchase Order (PO) directly. For purchases above €25,000, a formal Purchase Request (PR) must be submitted to Procurement.</span>\n      <a class=\"chip\" itemprop=\"url\" href=\"https://efg.coupahost.com/\">Coupa</a>\n    </li>\n\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Service\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Order-to-Pay (O2P)</strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">The O2P process covers supplier creation, PO approval, order fulfillment, and invoice processing. Invoices require an approved PO for payment.</span>\n      <a class=\"chip\" itemprop=\"url\" href=\"https://efg.coupahost.com/\">Coupa</a>\n      <a class=\"chip\" itemprop=\"url\" href=\"/wiki/spaces/PROC/pages/5595693076/Ensuring+Smooth+Payment+Process\">Ensuring Smooth Payment Process</a>\n    </li>\n\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Service\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Coupa Expenses</strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">Employees can submit expenses and credit card claims via Coupa. Managers are empowered to approve expenses up to 1K EUR for OPEX and 2.5K EUR for COGS. Supporting evidence, such as a tax invoice, must be submitted within 30 days.</span>\n      <a class=\"chip\" itemprop=\"url\" href=\"https://efg.coupahost.com/\">Coupa</a>\n    </li>\n\n    <li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Service\">\n      <strong itemprop=\"name\">Prize Money Payments</strong>\n      <span itemprop=\"description\">Prize money payouts for B2C and B2B are managed via the Payment Labs platform. Financial operations process the funding to the For Benefit Of (FBO) account, while tournament operations handle tournament setup and winner payment details.</span>\n      <a class=\"chip\" itemprop=\"url\" href=\"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/13tuxpLKWCnkux6A70uOughCATLrTWD8w?usp=drive_link\">Prize Money MEC Working</a>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>Finance Support and Contacts</h3>\n  <p>For general inquiries regarding Purchase Orders, Invoices, or Payments, please refer to the Coupa platform or contact the Finance Operations team.</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Finance Operations Lead:</strong> Sivakumar Govindan (<a href=\"mailto:s.govindan@efg.gg\">s.govindan@efg.gg</a>)</li>\n    <li><strong>System Errors:</strong> If you encounter errors in systems like Salesforce or Coupa, please contact the IT Helpdesk or the dedicated Slack channel, as Finance is not the appropriate department for system technical support.</li>\n  </ul>\n</section>",
                "Calendar": "<section>\n<h2>Finance Division Meeting and Calendar Structure</h2>\n<p>The Finance division operates under a structured meeting cadence designed to ensure strategic alignment, operational visibility, and effective communication across all teams. Specific dates and times for these recurring meetings are maintained in the external Finance calendar.</p>\n\n<h3>Recurring Cadences</h3>\n<ul class=\"efg-detail\">\n<li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Event\"><strong itemprop=\"name\">Finance Townhall <span class=\"efg-pill\">Quarterly</span></strong><span itemprop=\"description\">A department-wide session for company announcements, guest speakers, and individual/team achievements.</span></li>\n<li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Event\"><strong itemprop=\"name\">Leadership Pulse <span class=\"efg-pill\">Monthly</span></strong><span itemprop=\"description\">Focused on strategic alignment, escalation handling, and cascading information down to teams. Participants include L1-3 leadership.</span></li>\n<li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Event\"><strong itemprop=\"name\">Initiative Sync <span class=\"efg-pill\">Monthly</span></strong><span itemprop=\"description\">An operational meeting for L3 and below to provide visibility on project progress (using the Jira board) and highlight \"wins\".</span></li>\n<li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Event\"><strong itemprop=\"name\">Functional Tactical</strong><span itemprop=\"description\">Team-specific meetings led by Matt, Bassem, and Markus to align on day-to-day priorities, unblock tasks, and manage workload. Frequency to be determined by the lead of the department.</span></li>\n<li itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Event\"><strong itemprop=\"name\">1:1s <span class=\"efg-pill\">Weekly</span></strong><span itemprop=\"description\">Managers are required to maintain weekly 1:1 meetings with their direct reports.</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Sourcing Business Partner Schedules</h3>\n<ul class=\"efg-schedule\">\n<li><span class=\"n\">Publisher Operations</span><span class=\"t\">Wed · 3:30 PM GMT</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"n\">EWC/ENC</span><span class=\"t\">Wed · 09:00 PM GMT</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"n\">O&amp;O</span><span class=\"t\">Wed · 10:00 AM GMT</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"n\">MENA Operations</span><span class=\"t\">Thu · 10:00 AM GMT</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"n\">Enterprise Technology</span><span class=\"t\">Tue · 01:30 PM GMT</span></li>\n</ul>\n</section>",
