                "Extra": "<section itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/CreativeWork\">\n  <h2 itemprop=\"name\">Extra</h2>\n  <p itemprop=\"description\">Additional resources, governance frameworks, and support information for the Finance division.</p>\n\n  <h3>Finance Governance & Communication</h3>\n  <p>The Finance Governance and Communication framework defines our decision-making processes and information flow. This includes:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Communication Guidelines</li>\n    <li>Roles and Responsibilities</li>\n    <li>Department Townhall Meetings (Quarterly)</li>\n    <li>Department Reporting</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>Meeting Structure</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Finance Townhall (Quarterly):</strong> Department-wide session for company announcements, guest speakers, and achievements.</li>\n    <li><strong>Leadership Pulse (Monthly):</strong> Strategic alignment and escalation handling for L1-3 leadership.</li>\n    <li><strong>Initiative Sync (Monthly):</strong> Operational meeting for L3 and below to track project progress via Jira.</li>\n    <li><strong>Functional Tactical (Team dependent):</strong> Team-specific meetings led by Matt, Bassem, and Markus to align on day-to-day priorities.</li>\n    <li><strong>1:1s (Weekly):</strong> Managers are required to maintain weekly 1:1 meetings with their direct reports.</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <h3>Finance Templates</h3>\n  <p>To ensure consistency, standardized templates are available for Policies, Guidelines, SOPs, Process Descriptions, and RACM files. These are managed by Charlotta Hjalmarsson.</p>\n\n  <h3>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h3>\n  <p>For common queries, please consult the <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/13rnvLFe0nXmYVwnCD4pxqykEiRaF9TO5pY62oYRSW1k/edit?tab=t.0\">Finance FAQ document</a>. Note that Finance is not the correct department for system errors (e.g., Salesforce, Coupa, SAP) or project scope of work (SOW) inquiries; please refer to IT Helpdesk or your Project Manager respectively.</p>\n\n  <h3>Service Exceptions</h3>\n  <p>Certain services are managed outside of standard Finance procurement workflows:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Freelancers:</strong> Managed by Division.</li>\n    <li><strong>Audit Companies:</strong> Appointed by ARC.</li>\n    <li><strong>Legal Advisors:</strong> Controlled by Legal.</li>\n    <li><strong>Employee Benefits:</strong> Managed by HR.</li>\n    <li><strong>EOR / Payroll Services:</strong> Managed by HR / US ops team.</li>\n    <li><strong>Advertisement Services:</strong> Managed by Marketing.</li>\n    <li><strong>Players/Teams:</strong> Managed by Esports.</li>\n  </ul>\n</section>",
